<div class="customize">
  <h1 role="heading" aria-level="1">EMBED CODES AND SOCIAL SHARING</h1>
  
  <h2 role="heading" aria-level="2">Pick your embed code.</label></h2>
  <p>
   An embed code for each of Rock the Vote's civic tools is available below. 
   Copy the code and paste it into your website, blog or other web platform. 
   We recommend using this code as is: it will generate a "widget" that will keep 
   users on your website and lead to the highest completion rates. You can access 
   reports on these users by clicking the <%= link_to "Reports", statistics_partner_path(@partner) %> tab.
  </p>
  <p>You can include additional parameters with your embed codes. To view these parameters, go to the 
  <a href="https://www.rockthevote.org/programs-and-partner-resources/tech-for-civic-engagement/online-voter-registration-platform/partner-ovr-tool-faqs/" title="Getting Started with Your Voter Registration Tool">Civic Tech FAQs</a> 
  and look for "Ways to Use URL Parameters."
  </p>
  <p>
    Place the scripts tag in the &lt;body&gt; of your HTML where you want the interface to display.
  </p>

  <h3 role="heading" aria-level="3">Voter Registration embed code</h3>    
  <form class="copy_html" action="#" method="get" accept-charset="utf-8">       
    <div>
      <p><textarea name="js_src" readonly="readonly" rows="10" ><%= h @js_src_tag %>
<%= h @js_script %></textarea></p>      
      <p class="plain_text" style="display: none;">
        Other optional parameters include:
      </p>
      <p  style="display: none;"><textarea name="js_script" readonly="readonly" rows="10" >
source: "string",
tracking: "string",
state: "string", // 2-letter state abbreviation (capital letters) e.g. "CA"
home_zip_code: "string", // 5-digit zip code
email_address: "string",
first_name: "string",
last_name: "string",
locale: "string" // 2-letter locale code (lower case) e.g. "es"
      </textarea></p>
    </div>
  </form>
  
